
#sample-media-queries
  h4 Media queries

  p.align-justify.
    Media queries allows us to make an even more accurated design. In <code >seed-css</code>
    they are made to represent the following screen sizes:

  .table-responsive 
    table
      thead
        tr
          th &nbsp;
          th Screen width
          th Prefix
          th Columns
          th Container
      tbody
        tr
          td.nowrap Mobiles
          td.nowrap
            strong &lt; 600px
          td.nowrap
            strong .sm
          td
            strong 12
          td
            strong 90%
        tr
          td.nowrap Tablets
          td.nowrap
            strong &lt;= 990px
          td.nowrap
            strong .md
          td
            strong 12
          td
            strong 85%
        tr
          td.nowrap Desktops/ laptops
          td.nowrap
            strong &lt;= 1200px
          td.nowrap
            strong .lg
          td
            strong 12
          td
            strong 80%
        tr
          td.nowrap Extra large desktops/TVs
          td.nowrap
            strong &gt; 1200px
          td.nowrap
            strong .xl
          td
            strong 12
          td
            strong 75%

  p.align-justify.
    You can safely write your own styling rules using the following queries and keep covered by
    <code >seed-css</code> grid system. Using a different set of media queries may
    overwrite this boilerplate grid system.

  .table-responsive 
    table
      thead
        tr
          th Query
          th Remarks
      tbody
        tr
          td @media only screen and (min-width: 0px)
          td For mobile devices. (Mobile first)
        tr
          td @media only screen and (min-width: 600px)
          td For tablets devices.
        tr
          td @media only screen and (min-width: 990px)
          td For desktop/ laptop devices.
        tr
          td @media only screen and (min-width: 1200px)
          td For extra large desktop/ TV devices.

  .code-sample
    pre.prettyprint.lang-css.
      // Mobile first
      @media only screen and (min-width: 0px) {
        ...
      }

      // Tablets
      @media only screen and (min-width: 600px) {
        ...
      }

      // Desktops/ Laptops
      @media only screen and (min-width: 990px) {
        ...
      }

      // Extra large desktops/ TVs
      @media only screen and (min-width: 1200px) {
        ...
      }
